        "text": "Relationships with the media can be of different kinds. The one that kinda pushes itself forward in this (cultural) space seems to be 'open learning' conducted as 'distance learning' via delivered courses to cohorts of students and repos of open-access media - for example, MOOCs (massive open online courses). There's a curriculum, there might be master-classes or gurus or talking heads; there's an audience. There might be certification. This maybe kinda makes sense if, for example, there is an attempt at propagation of 'a common culture', or transmission of a 'legacy' or 'canon'. Maybe it makes sense is people want to 'just learn' in a somewhat passive way. Open-source tools - actually, assemblages of tools (a mini-toolstack) - like Moodle and Canvas, are in this space."
